Pour the water for the rice (see pantry for amount) into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Trim the @green beans{80%g}(trimmed), then cut into thirds.

Halve any thick @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g}(halved and cut into thirds) stems lengthways, then cut into thirds.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion, beans, broccoli and @THIS™ Isn't Chicken Plant-Based Pieces{170%g}.

Fry until the veg has softened and the THIS™ Isn't Chicken is golden brown, ~{6-8%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the garlic and @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} to the pan and fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @Ketjap Manis{50%g}, @Rice Vinegar{30%ml}, @Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{100%ml}. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Share the rice between your bowls.

Spoon over the stir-fried sweet and sticky THIS™ Isn't Chicken and veg.

Sprinkle over the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%g} to finish.

Enjoy!